      <hedline>
        <hl1>'Personal Virtue' And Energy Policy</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James A Daley III letter, commenting on May 1 article, disputes assertion by Vice Pres Dick Cheney that energy conservation is a personal virtue</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cheney Promotes Increasing Supply as Energy Policy'' (front page, May 1):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Cheney Promotes Increasing Supply as Energy Policy'' (front page, May 1):</p>
        <p>Improved energy conservation is not a ''personal virtue,'' as the vice president suggests. Rather, in tandem with development of renewable energy sources, it provides a middle path to protect clean air, pristine wilderness areas and still meet our country's need for energy.</p>
        <p>JAMES A. DALEY III  Boston, May 1, 2001</p>
        <p>The writer is coordinator, Appalachian Partnership for Eastern Forests.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
